Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and classification of text data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the influence of online social networks on the spread of fake news. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with selecting relevant features for fake news detection. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper investigates multiple types of classifiers for fake news detection. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as detecting fake news can have implications for security and privacy.
